  "texts": [
    "To maximize performance, transfer learning allows leveraging pre-trained DL models trained on other datasets (e.g., natural images) to enhance performance on fossil image analysis, especially in data-constrained scenarios.",
    "CNNs are specialized deep neural networks optimized for analyzing grid-like data, particularly images.",
    "The term 'deep' refers to the network's architecture, which consists of multiple layers.",
    "These layers allow the network to learn increasingly abstract representations of the data as it moves through each layer.",
    "The core functionality of CNNs is rooted in their ability to perform convolution operations, which involve the application of a convolutional kernel to multi-dimensional arrays/tensors."
